o|Social Democratic Party]]\n|leader              = [[Ivan Brajovi\u0107]]\n|foundation          = 31 July 2015\n|ideology            = [[Social democracy]]<ref name=\"PAE\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parties-and-elections.eu/montenegro.html|website=Parties and Elections in Europe|title=Montenegro|first=Wolfram|last=Nordsieck|year=2016|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref><br>[[Social liberalism]]<br>[[Atlanticism]]<br />[[Pro-Europeanism]]\n|position            = [[Centrism|Centre]] to [[Centre-left politics|centre-left]]\n|headquarters        = [[Podgorica]]\n|colorcode           = {{Social Democrats of Montenegro/meta/color}}\n|seats1_title        = [[Parliament of Montenegro|Parliament]]\n|seats1              = {{Composition bar|2|81|hex={{Social Democrats of Montenegro/meta/color}}}}\n|seats2_title       = [[Municipalities of Montenegro|Local Parliaments]]\n|seats2             = {{Composition bar|63|786|hex={{Social Democrats of Montenegro/meta/color}}}}\n|website             = [https://sdcg.me www.sdcg.me]\n}}\n\n'''Social Democrats of Montenegro''' ([[Montenegrin language|Montenegrin]]: ''Socijaldemokrate Crne Gore'', ''\u0421\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0458\u0430\u043b\u0434\u0435\u043c\u043e\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0435 \u0426\u0440\u043d\u0435 \u0413\u043e\u0440\u0435'', ''SD CG''), or just the '''Social Democrats''' ([[Montenegrin language|Montenegrin]]: Socijaldemokrate, \u0421\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0458\u0430\u043b\u0434\u0435\u043c\u043e\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0442e, '''SD'''), is a [[centre-left]] [[List of political parties in Montenegro|political party]] in [[Montenegro]] formed in 2015 by a split faction of [[Social Democratic Party of Montenegro]]. ''SD'' is one of the ruling parties in Montenegro with the [[President of the Parliament of Montenegro|President of the Parliament]] and two ministers. It currently has two representatives in the [[Parliament of Montenegro]], [[2016 Montenegrin parliamentary election|elected in 2016]].\n\n==History==\nThe party was founded in July 2015<ref name=\"vijesti.me Founding Document\">[http://www.vijesti.me/vijesti/socijaldemokrate-crne-gore-nova-partija-841975 Socijaldemokrate Crne Gore nova partija ]</ref> after the split between two [[Social Democratic Party of Montenegro|Social Democratic Party]] (SDP) vice-presidents Vujica Lazovi\u0107 and Ivan Brajovi\u0107, that advocated unconditional support for the ruling [[Democratic Party of Socialists]] (DPS) and Prime Minister [[Milo \u0110ukanovi\u0107]] with the party leader [[Ranko Krivokapi\u0107]], who advocated pursuing an independent political course.<ref name=\"aljazeera.net Founding Document\">[http://balkans.aljazeera.net/vijesti/crna-gora-raskol-u-sdp-u-upitna-koalicija Crna Gora: Raskol u SDP-u, upitna koalicija ]</ref><ref name=\"slobodnaevropa.org Founding Document\">[http://www.slobodnaevropa.org/content/sdp-opstaje-a-ko-odlazi/27102328.html Raskol u SDP: Brajovi\u0107eva struja napustila stranku, Krivokapi\u0107 tra\u017ei da vrate mandate]</ref> [[Ivan Brajovi\u0107]], Minister of Transport and Maritime Affairs in [[Government of Montenegro]] at the time, was chosen as the first president of the new party. After 2016 parliamentary election, party won two seats in the [[Parliament of Montenegro]], remain part of the government with two ministers while the Party leader Brajovi\u0107 was elected [[President of the Parliament of Montenegro]].\n\n==Elections==\n===Parliamentary elections===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ [[Parliament of Montenegro]]\n! Year\n! Popular vote\n! % of popular vote\n! Overall seats won\n! Seat change\n! Government\n|-\n! [[2012 Montenegrin parliamentary election|2015]]\n| colspan=2|Split from [[Social Democratic Party of Montenegro|Social Democratic Party]]\n| {{Infobox political party/seats|3|81|hex={{Social Democrats of Montenegro/meta/color}}}}\n| {{increase}} 3\n| {{yes|government}}\n|-\n! [[2016 Montenegrin parliamentary election|2016]]\n| 12,472\n| 3.26%\n| {{Infobox political party/seats|2|81|hex={{Social Democrats of Montenegro/meta/color}}}}\n| {{decrease}} 1\n| {{yes|government}}\n|}\n\n==Presidential elections==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ [[President of Montenegro]]\n! Election year\n! Candidate\n! #\n! 1st round votes\n! %\n! #\n! 2nd round votes\n! %\n! Note\n|-\n! [[2018 Montenegrin presidential election|2018]]\n|''[[Milo \u0110ukanovi\u0107]]''\n| {{yes|1st}}\n| ''180,274''\n| ''53.90%''\n| {{n/a}}\n| ''\u2014''\n| ''\u2014''\n| [[Democratic Party of Socialists|DPS]], support\n|-\n|}\n\n==Positions held==\nMajor positions held by Social Democrats of Montenegro members:\n\n{| class=wikitable\n! [[President of the Parliament of Montenegro]] !! Years\n|-\n|[[Ivan Brajovi\u0107]]\n|2016-incumbent\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Montenegrin political parties}}\n\n[[Category:2015 establishments in Montenegro]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2015]]\n[[Category:Pro-European political parties in Montenegro]]\n[[Category:Social democratic parties in Montenegro]]\n\n\n{{Montenegro-party-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WalterII", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_Democrats_of_Montenegro"}
